WEBVTT



00:00:02.688 --> 00:00:07.200
And really that's all that we've wanted to do today is to tell the story again.

00:00:07.328 --> 00:00:09.472
The story of the Christ-child.

00:00:09.632 --> 00:00:12.448
The story of the one who came to help us all.

00:00:12.320 --> 00:00:14.464
Find our way home.

00:00:14.848 --> 00:00:18.080
And home is a place of safety and security.

00:00:18.112 --> 00:00:19.584
And provision.

00:00:19.936 --> 00:00:21.120
And hope.

00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:29.472
you know the reality is all of us are wanderers just a little bit and some of us are wandering a lot trying to make sense of life.

00:00:29.184 --> 00:00:34.336
Trying to make sense of the journey, trying to find our own ways home.

00:00:34.240 --> 00:00:37.984
At times we all feel a little bit lost and sometimes we feel

00:00:37.792 --> 00:00:40.288
A whole lot lost.

00:00:42.752 --> 00:00:44.736
we sense that daniel

00:00:45.408 --> 00:00:47.264
Was on a search for home.

00:00:49.472 --> 00:00:50.816
We believe

00:00:51.712 --> 00:00:53.024
That he alone,

00:00:52.864 --> 00:00:54.560
God was the one

00:00:54.496 --> 00:00:56.832
Who could help him find his way home?

00:00:57.024 --> 00:00:58.592
And we see Daniel.

00:00:58.592 --> 00:01:01.696
exchanging the security of life and

00:01:02.592 --> 00:01:04.160
A royal palace.

00:01:04.960 --> 00:01:08.512
To join the holy family in a refugee-like journey.

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:13.600
But we heard him say,

00:01:14.528 --> 00:01:16.960
I found my home not in a place.

00:01:18.976 --> 00:01:20.672
But in a relationship.

00:01:21.632 --> 00:01:23.168
With the Christ child.

00:01:25.984 --> 00:01:27.936
What we wanted to do today

00:01:27.872 --> 00:01:31.936
is to invite you into a journey that makes room for faith.

00:01:31.936 --> 00:01:34.560
Makes room for the mysterious.

00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:35.872
In life.

00:01:36.512 --> 00:01:39.456
For some of us, faith comes easy, and for others,

00:01:39.936 --> 00:01:41.280
Not so much.

00:01:42.464 --> 00:01:45.024
One philosophical soul wrote that

00:01:44.896 --> 00:01:47.872
There ain't no journey that don't change you some.

00:01:48.736 --> 00:01:50.688
and the journey toward belief.

00:01:51.392 --> 00:01:53.056
Changes us plenty.

00:01:53.920 --> 00:01:55.712
But it's a good change.

00:01:57.632 --> 00:02:00.032
Sometimes it seems impossible.

00:02:00.608 --> 00:02:04.064
To believe that God could come in the form of a baby.

00:02:04.352 --> 00:02:07.232
To change the world, but we know it to be true.

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:11.584
i was visiting just the other day with a young family with a.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:13.952
Little toddler, perhaps.

00:02:14.592 --> 00:02:19.232
The age of our baby Jesus, and was he not the star of the show?

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:20.352
Yes.

00:02:20.064 --> 00:02:21.312
today.

00:02:21.504 --> 00:02:25.408
And this little one is learning to walk and is taking her first steps.

00:02:25.472 --> 00:02:30.400
And I watched this mom and dad so thrilled with these infant steps.

00:02:30.592 --> 00:02:32.480
But there to catch her.

00:02:32.960 --> 00:02:40.960
and she was completely fearless. it was the ultimate trust fall. she would fall forward and backward knowing that her mom or her dad or both of them.

00:02:40.864 --> 00:02:42.592
Were there to catch her.

00:02:42.976 --> 00:02:44.672
And to keep her safe.

00:02:45.408 --> 00:02:48.128
And in many ways, that is the message of Christmas.

00:02:48.576 --> 00:02:50.048
That he is here.

00:02:49.888 --> 00:02:53.152
He's Emmanuel, that God is with us.

00:02:52.928 --> 00:02:55.072
To catch us when we stumble.

00:02:55.712 --> 00:02:58.368
To protect us when we fall.

00:02:59.104 --> 00:03:01.792
And to help us walk steps of faith.

00:03:02.016 --> 00:03:04.864
That give us a profound sense that we are home.

00:03:05.248 --> 00:03:06.592
And that all

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:08.384
Is well,

00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:12.128
Jesus' journey to Bethlehem.

00:03:13.248 --> 00:03:14.880
To become our Emmanuel.

00:03:16.224 --> 00:03:19.584
If we, as meek souls, will receive him still.

00:03:20.544 --> 00:03:30.592
And in that carol that we love to sing and that we'll sing on Christmas Eve. And if you have no service to join in on, I encourage you to come back and join us. We'll have three services, one at three and one at 430.

00:03:30.112 --> 00:03:32.352
And one at 6 o'clock. Yeah.

00:03:32.896 --> 00:03:40.672
But we'll most likely sing a holy night. And there's a line in that hymn that utterly thrills my heart and captures the message of today.

00:03:41.408 --> 00:03:43.200
That till he appeared,

00:03:43.456 --> 00:03:45.920
Then the soul felt its worth.

00:03:46.464 --> 00:03:49.696
And when we embrace Jesus, we discover

00:03:51.136 --> 00:03:52.352
Are worth.

00:03:52.544 --> 00:03:54.176
Why we were made.

00:03:54.336 --> 00:03:57.664
And what it means to be home, you might appear to have everything.

00:03:58.944 --> 00:04:01.408
Perhaps like Bardia or Haxanen.

00:04:02.880 --> 00:04:04.960
But everything with our God has a way of...

00:04:06.016 --> 00:04:07.552
Becoming not enough.

00:04:08.384 --> 00:04:12.064
Christmas is God's secret invitation to come and find Jesus.

00:04:12.256 --> 00:04:13.952
To come and find.

00:04:13.728 --> 00:04:14.912
Enough.

00:04:15.840 --> 00:04:18.176
Come and find the God who loves us.

00:04:18.464 --> 00:04:20.352
That he came to this planet.

00:04:20.448 --> 00:04:21.952
To join with us.

00:04:22.048 --> 00:04:24.512
In this world that he created.

00:04:25.056 --> 00:04:27.104
And to help us find our way home.

00:04:27.648 --> 00:04:31.424
In a moment there will be one last song, some spoken word.

00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:41.408
There'll be an opportunity for us to express appreciation to the cast, and we will receive an offering, and the offering is a church service for us here at Foothills. And if you're a guest, we don't want you

00:04:40.928 --> 00:04:50.112
Want you to feel any sense of obligation? You're welcome to give if you choose, but your presence here today has really been your gift to us and we're very grateful for that.

00:04:50.240 --> 00:04:53.312
And if I could indulge myself just a little bit,

00:04:53.216 --> 00:04:55.008
Us all, perhaps,

00:04:55.648 --> 00:04:58.720
As I said earlier, these things don't just happen.

00:04:58.976 --> 00:05:06.080
It's a remarkable amount of work and effort and commitment and passion and prayer that makes something like this take place.

00:05:06.080 --> 00:05:08.032
And I just want to take my

00:05:08.192 --> 00:05:12.960
This opportunity for myself to say thank you as well. I'll say thank you in a moment.

00:05:13.600 --> 00:05:14.848
but to adam.

00:05:15.104 --> 00:05:15.968
Who's who's

00:05:15.712 --> 00:05:24.032
last summer while we were in beaches and vacations and enjoying quiet time adam was thinking of christmas and riding away fervently.

00:05:24.256 --> 00:05:28.288
So Mark and Rebecca, who took a brilliant script,

00:05:28.192 --> 00:05:38.240
and somehow made it come alive even more to the actors, to the people behind the scenes. they'll point up to the booth and and the sound, the music that was written, the.

00:05:37.760 --> 00:05:47.808
The effects, the lighting, all the people that are behind moving pieces, the kids that manage not to fall out of the thing as they look at it.

00:05:47.328 --> 00:05:52.288
than elevated the cloth to the

00:05:52.160 --> 00:05:53.632
So many.

00:05:53.696 --> 00:05:55.488
Who gave so much?

00:05:56.096 --> 00:05:58.144
To make this possible.

00:05:58.048 --> 00:06:01.376
One of the cast members, mother, is deathly ill.

00:06:01.600 --> 00:06:04.384
And the thought is she won't make it through the weekend.

00:06:04.576 --> 00:06:11.360
And yet she has served with faith and grace and hope and peace, and somehow found comfort in the message.

00:06:11.360 --> 00:06:14.720
That is the commitment of those who have served us this weekend.

00:06:14.912 --> 00:06:16.640
and in a few moments.

00:06:16.224 --> 00:06:22.528
I hope that we will profoundly express gratitude, not just for a fantastic theater production,

00:06:22.720 --> 00:06:24.256
But for a message.

00:06:24.672 --> 00:06:26.656
That leads us home.

00:06:27.424 --> 00:06:31.200
And gives us peace. So let me pray. The ushers will come.

00:06:31.008 --> 00:06:34.528
We'll have the last song. If you know the words, join in. Thank you.

00:06:34.976 --> 00:06:45.024
as we celebrate the gift of God. You are good and kind, Father. You have blessed us abundantly. It has been good to be here. And thank you that in the craziness of a Canadian December,

00:06:44.544 --> 00:06:53.600
you've brought us peace, hope, perspective to help us understand not just the wonder of the gift but the purpose of the gift to lead us home.

00:06:53.376 --> 00:06:55.104
We say thank you.

00:06:55.008 --> 00:06:58.848
We make room for the Christ child, not just in our Christmas.

00:06:59.328 --> 00:07:00.960
But in our lives.

00:07:01.472 --> 00:07:03.328
We choose to bow down.

00:07:03.584 --> 00:07:04.768
And worship.

00:07:05.088 --> 00:07:06.464
And trust.

00:07:06.720 --> 00:07:07.968
And follow.

00:07:08.576 --> 00:07:11.424
Thank you for being so good and kind.

00:07:11.456 --> 00:07:12.768
And faithful.

00:07:13.056 --> 00:07:14.432
We bless you.

00:07:14.528 --> 00:07:15.872
In Jesus.

00:07:16.192 --> 00:07:17.408
The priest,

00:07:17.504 --> 00:07:18.592
The king.

00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:20.320
The Savior's name.

00:07:20.128 --> 00:07:21.088
I pray.
